com.martinandersson.money.unittest

Class PriceSerializationTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.martinandersson.money.unittest.PriceSerializationTest

  • public class PriceSerializationTest
extends java.lang.Object
    Will unit test serialization frameworks for different versions of Price, ensuring serialization and deserialization work properly as well as print their serialized byte size and serialization time cost.

    Don't take the time cost results of this class too seriously. Firstly, the time cost will vary quit a lot from execution to execution. Also as demonstrated in other tests and benchmarks, the performance change significantly once we start serializing/deserializing thousands of prices.

    What can be said about the results of this class is that Kryo is the unbeaten winner for every Price implementation when it comes to saving bytes.

    The JavaDoc of all methods herein list the results produced by author's machine.

    The winner in terms of disk space is FastMoneyPrice combined with SerializationFramework.KRYO_CUSTOM.

    However, a real application may go even further on its quest to save bytes. The FastMoneyPrice#date field is already present in the map as the entry key. Hence, this field could be marked transient.
